# EXStreamTV Critical Rules — Never Violate

Full rules:   .cursor/rules/exstreamtv-safety.mdc
Full lessons: docs/LESSONS_LEARNED.md

1. datetime     — always datetime.now(tz=timezone.utc), never utcnow(). Normalise DB values with _ensure_utc() before arithmetic.
2. FFmpeg flags — always import from exstreamtv/ffmpeg/constants.py. Never hardcode. Never -flags +low_delay or +fastseek.
3. H.264 COPY   — always add -bsf:v h264_mp4toannexb after -c:v copy into MPEG-TS. Non-optional.
4. async + DB   — never call sync SQLAlchemy .execute() or .commit() directly inside async def. Always run_in_executor.
5. async lock   — never await inside async with self._lock. Collect under lock, execute outside.
6. XMLTV time   — always %Y%m%d%H%M%S +0000. No dashes, no colons, no UTC suffix.
7. sched loop   — every while loop advancing a time cursor must have an else guard that advances the index and breaks on full wrap.
8. MPEG-TS trim — always find 0x47 sync byte and align before yielding trimmed bytes.
